# Prompt Eval Hook

When modifying any AI-facing prompt (skill file, agent command, or system prompt), follow this process:

## Activation

This rule applies when you are:
- Editing a `SKILL.md` file in `.claude/skills/` or `.agents/skills/`
- Editing a command file in `.cursor/commands/`
- Editing prompt templates in any `prompts/` directory
- Modifying eval suites or criteria in `evals/`

This rule does NOT apply to:
- Editing cursor rules (`.mdc` files in `.cursor/rules/`)
- Editing documentation or READMEs
- Editing source code that doesn't contain prompts

## Process

### 1. Check for an existing eval suite
Look for `evals/<prompt-name>/eval-suite.yaml`. If one exists, any prompt changes should be re-evaluated.

### 2. If no eval suite exists
Read `.claude/skills/prompt-eval-framework/SKILL.md` and create one before making prompt changes. Minimum: 5 test cases, 3 criteria.

### 3. After making prompt changes
- Increment the version number
- Save the new prompt version (never overwrite)
- Run the eval suite using the `/prompt-eval` command
- Compare scores against the previous version
- Only finalize if the new version scores equal to or higher than the previous
